This paper discusses the use of bibliometric methods to study the humanities, which involves analyzing publications and citations. This topic is relevant to several sub-categories in computer science, including digital libraries (cs.DL), information retrieval (cs.IR), social and information networks (cs.SI), human-computer interaction (cs.HC), and computers and society (cs.CY).
